## Summary

**E4: Media Pool & Audio Storage** - fully implemented and shipped.

### What was built (27 files, +1950 lines):

**Core audio module** (`src/audio/media-pool/`):
- **types.ts** - MediaPool, AudioSourceHandle, WaveformPeaks, MediaPoolError (discriminated union)
- **magic-bytes.ts** - File format detection from first 12 bytes (WAV/MP3/OGG/FLAC)
- **idb-storage.ts** - IndexedDB persistence + in-memory test implementation
- **decode-pipeline.ts** - decodeAudioData with 500MB limit, magic-bytes validation, error results
- **waveform-peaks.ts** - Min/max peak computation across channels
- **media-pool-manager.ts** - Orchestrates import, storage, retrieval, deletion
- **Context/Provider/Hook** - React integration following existing pattern

**UI** (`src/ui/media-pool/`):
- **MediaPoolPanel** - Panel with drag-drop, file picker, error display
- **MediaPoolItem** - Row with waveform preview, duration, format badge, delete
- **WaveformPreview** - Canvas-based waveform thumbnail
- **useFileDrop** - Drag-and-drop hook

**Integration**: App.tsx wraps DawShell in MediaPoolProvider; DawShell renders MediaPoolPanel alongside InstrumentPanel.

